ENTRY            E2816   20260226   20260227   20260227       E155
SUBENT        E2816001   20260226   20260227   20260227       E155
BIB                 12         26
TITLE      Discovery of Proton-Rich Radioactive Isotopes in the Z
           = 60 Region Produced by the Projectile Fragmentation
           of a 345-MeV/Nucleon 238U Beam
AUTHOR     (H.Suzuki, N.Fukuda, H.Takeda, Y.Shimizu, M.Yoshimoto,
            Y.Togano, H.Sato, N.Kitamura, S.Hanai, S.Momota,
            K.Kusaka, Y.Yanagisawa, M.Ohtake, T.Sumikama,
            N.Fukunishi, S.Michimasa)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNIPC,2JPNTOK,2JPNKUT)
REFERENCE  (J,PTEP,2025,113D01,2025)
INC-SOURCE Beam intensity is 55 to 60 particle-nA.
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
           - Target-thickness: 1 mm
METHOD     (TOFDE)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNIPC) RIBF
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,SCIN) BigRIPS
           (IOCH)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The systematic error was estimated from the
                   fluctuation of the deduced cross sections of
                   RIs whose cross sections were measured by
                   different settings.
           (DATA-ERR) No information on source of uncertainties
STATUS     (TABLE,,H.Suzuki+,J,PTEP,2025,113D01,2025) Plotted in
                                                      Fig. 6
HISTORY    (20251218R) Received by e-mail from Dr. H. Suzuki.
           (20251223C) MA
ENDBIB              26
COMMON               2          3
EN         ERR-1
MEV/A      PER-CENT
 345.       20.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           33
SUBENT        E2816002   20260226   20260227   20260227       E155
BIB                  2          5
REACTION   (4-BE-9(92-U-238,X)ELEM/MASS,,SIG)
FLAG       (1.) 119Ce setting
           (2.) 124Nd setting
           (3.) 123Ce-W setting
           (4.) 123Ce-N setting
ENDBIB               5
